#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/gnupg-user.xml:359
#, no-wrap
msgid "Exchanging keys with keyservers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gnupg-user.xml:361
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sending keys to keyservers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gnupg-user.xml:365
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that you have your key, it is probably a good idea to send it to the world\n"
"key server. There are a lot of keyservers in the world and most of them exchange\n"
"keys between them. Here we are going to send John Doe's key to the\n"
"subkeys.pgp.net server. This uses HTTP, so if you need to use a proxy for HTTP\n"
"traffic don't forget to set it (<c>export\n"
"http_proxy=http://proxy_host:port/</c>). The command for sending the key is:\n"
"<c>gpg --keyserver subkeys.pgp.net --keyserver-options honor-http-proxy\n"
"--send-key 75447B14</c> where <c>75447B14</c> is the key ID.  If you don't need\n"
"a HTTP proxy you can remove the <e>--keyserver-options honor-http-proxy</e>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gnupg-user.xml:377
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can also send other people's keys that you have signed to the keyserver. We\n"
"could send Luis Pinto's key to the keyserver. This way someone who trusts\n"
"your key can use the signature that you have placed there to trust Luis's key.\n"
msgstr ""

